Peter Obi, the Labour Party (LP) presidential candidate, and Datti Baba-Ahmed, his running mate, were at the Tafawa Balewa Square as the party held its presidential campaign rally in Lagos. Earlier on Saturday, Obi was received at the Alaba international market in Lagos by a large crowd of supporters before heading to the venue of the rally. Ayo Adebanjo, leader of Afenifere, a Yoruba socio-cultural group; Gbadebo Rhodes-Vivour, LP governorship candidate in Lagos; Aisha Yesufu, an activist; Julius Abure, LP national chair; Doyin Okupe, LP chieftain; and Pat Utomi, professor of political economy, were all in attendance. See photos below.                                     